Class Tile

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Tile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChangesObservable
    public class Tile
extends java.lang.Object
implements ChangesObservable
    The Tile class is the element that constitutes a GameMap. A Tile contains the reference of the adjacent tiles in the map. All the adjacent tiles are different ( example: northTile and SouthTile can't both point to the same object). A tile contains the players that are placed in it. A boolean field indicate if contains ammo or weapons. A Tile can have a reference to a tile that is not connected, but that is only separated by a wall. The "walled" fields store this reference, and can be null (for example, if the wall is one of the edges of the map, of course there isn't a tile in the wall),

      • getTilesDirectionBehindWall

        public java.util.List<Tile> getTilesDirectionBehindWall​(java.lang.String dir)
        Returns a list of all the tiles in a given direction. The walls are ignored. So A->B | C would return [A,B,C], while the getTilesDirection would have returned [A,B]. This list in never empty, since the tile of the player is always returned
        Parameters:
        dir - can only be "north", "east", "south", "west"
        Returns:
        a list of tiles (is never empty, the tile in the player is always in).
